<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,915,2020]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
The description of the 
<typeStatus box="[460,564,988,1012]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Holotype</typeStatus>
was done many years ago, and some characters described in related species were not recorded at the time. Unfortunately I have not seen any other specimens. The specimen was not dissected and although labelled as 
<specimenCount box="[429,450,1060,1083]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, the quadrate distal antennal segments would suggest that the specimen might be 
<specimenCount box="[1366,1387,1060,1083]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
